               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410614-name-960" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410614-name-960" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410614-name-960" type="surname" value="GILLMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410614-name-960" type="given" value="EDWARD JAMES"></interp>EDWARD JAMES GILLMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a grocer, and live in Crown-street, Finsbury. On the morning of the 3rd of June I had occasion to leave my shop at half-past seven o'clock—I returned in a few minutes, and found the prisoner coming from behind the counter, hanging his hands down—I asked what was in his hand, and took from his hands two half-crowns—I went to my till, and found two half-crowns gone from it—I sent for a policeman—he said nothing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
